                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d215">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 D 811/10a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Commissioner at Berlin</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dresel</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-09T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>920. Department is considering designation of you and Grant-Smith as High
                    Commissioners. However such a change in your case at this time might give German
                    Government an excuse for suggesting that it send a Commissioner here.
                    Furthermore, it is understood that as representatives at Berlin from other
                    nations have diplomatic rank, there is not the contrast between High
                    Commissioner and Commissioner as exists at Budapest. Cable frankly your
                    preference and views on advisability of such change.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
